    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>You may need to check to see that the string is at least 3 characters long and not <code>null</code> first.</p>\n\n<pre><code>if (millesecondsD != null &amp;&amp; millisecondsD.length() &gt;=3)\n    millesecondsD = milisecondsD.substring(milisecondsD.length() - 3);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Also, you can leave off the second parameter if you want.</p>\n\n<p>Example:</p>\n\n<pre><code>String:\nI'm a chunky monkey from funky town\n01234567890123456789012345678901234\n         10        20        30\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>So, in this case the last 3 chars are 34, 33, and 32.  The indices you have in your code are correct.</p>\n"
