  "title" : "Get right part of string in Android app",
  "body" : "<p>Ok, I am trying to get the right three characters of a string in an Android app I'm writing.</p>\n\n<p>Based on the research I've done in the SDK and online I should be able to use something like the following to do it.</p>\n\n<pre><code>millisecondsD = millisecondsD.substring(millisecondsD.length() -3, millisecondsD.length());\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>However, I get a force close whenever I try to use to use the code above.  Am I just missing something super simple?</p>\n"
